PENALTY :
Section 471 of the Liquor Code [47 P.S. Â§4-471] prescribes a penalty of license suspension or revocation or a fine of not less than $50.00 or more than $1,000.00 or both for violations of the type found in this case.
Licensee is put on notice that it faces progressively harsh penalties for further violations of this type.
Licensee requested that a suspension in lieu of a fine be imposed in this case.
After due consideration of the circumstances giving rise to the citation, a one day suspension will be imposed.
ORDER:
THEREFORE, IT IS HEREBY ORDERED that the club liquor license of Home Association of V.F.W. of Freeport No. 6648, License No.
C-4873 be suspended for a period of one day BEGINNING at 7:00 a.m. on Monday, February 22, 1999 and ENDING at 7:00 a.m. on Tuesday, February 23, 1999.
Licensee is directed on Monday, February 22, 1999 at 7:00 a.m. to place the enclosed placard of notice of suspension (identified as Form No.
PLCB-1925 and as printed with red and black ink) in a conspicuous place on the outside of the licensed premises or in a window plainly visible from outside the licensed premises and to remove said license from the wall and place it in a secure location.
Licensee is advised if replacement placards are needed for any reason they are available at all Pennsylvania Liquor Stores/Wine 
The Bureau is directed to visit and monitor the aforementioned licensed premises for compliance with this Order.
Licensee is authorized on Tuesday, February 23, 1999 at 7:00 a.m. to remove the placard of suspension and return the license to its original wall location.
Dated this day of ________________________, 1998.
